S'Nationwide Mobile Banking makes managing your money on the move easy.  Exclusively available to our Internet Bank customers, you can register and log in to the Mobile Banking app using your existing Internet Bank details. Features:With the Nationwide Mobile Banking app you can:\xe2\x80\xa2\tView your current account, savings, credit card and mortgage balances\xe2\x80\xa2\tView recent current account, savings and credit card transactions & statements\xe2\x80\xa2\tTransfer money between your Nationwide accounts\xe2\x80\xa2\tMake payments to existing payeesTo register you\xe2\x80\x99ll need to:\xe2\x80\xa2\tDownload the app\xe2\x80\xa2\tLog in using your Internet Banking log in details including your customer number, memorable data and passnumber or card and card reader.The next time you log in after registering all you\xe2\x80\x99ll need is your Internet Banking passnumber.If you\xe2\x80\x99re not yet a registered Internet Bank user, simply go to www.nationwide.co.uk/register and follow the on screen instructions. Once you\xe2\x80\x99ve received your Internet Banking log in details, you\xe2\x80\x99ll be able to download and register to use the Mobile Banking app also.Staying safeNationwide uses the latest security technologies to ensure that our customers are safe and secure when using the app.  Our digital promise means that you will never lose a penny if you are the victim of fraud whilst using Nationwide\xe2\x80\x99s digital services.In addition there are a few things you can do to help protect yourself when using the app:\xe2\x80\xa2\tNever share your login details with anyone\xe2\x80\xa2\tWhen logging in in a public place be careful to keep your details out of sightFor details of the full promise please visit this site www.nationwide.co.uk/IBpromiseImportant informationWe won\xe2\x80\x99t charge you for using this app but your mobile operator may charge you for some services such as data exchange, so please check with them.  It is not possible to view MySave accounts using the app, please log into your MySave account via the internet.  Customers who have only MySave accounts with Nationwide will not be able to use the app.Nationwide Building Society is authorised and regulated by the Financial Services Authority under registration number 106078. Credit facilities other than regulated mortgages are not regulated by the Financial Services Authority. You can confirm our registration on the FSA\xe2\x80\x99s website, www.fsa.gov.uk, or by contacting the FSA on 0845 606 1234.Terms and conditions for the Nationwide Mobile Banking app can be found at http://www.nationwide.co.uk/mobile-banking/legal.htmContact usFor details of how to contact us, please visit www.nationwide.co.uk/contact_usRecent changes:Minor bug fixes to improve customer experience'
